pageContext.claim: “We won 196-to-nothing in the House. This was not supposed to happen. But I have great confidence in the Republicans and the Republican Senate and I know they're going to be fair.”
pageContext.analysis: The House voted 230-197 to impeach Trump for abuse of power in his dealings with Ukraine and 229-198 on charges of obstructing Congress's investigation. All 196 Republicans voted nay.
